    "text": "By By COLTON KEMP ,\n5 days ago More people incarcerated at Minnesota’s largest state prison signed up to volunteer than there were spaces available during a recent meal-packing event with Meals from the Heart.\nFrom left, Ricardo Roque and Bonifacio Languren package meals during an event Thursday morning at the Minnesota Correctional Facility-Faribault with Meals From The Heart, which will be donated to Ruth’s House and Sarah’s House. (Colton Kemp/southernminn.com) Meals From The Heart volunteers, from left, Wayne Pepin and Randy Ludtke bring more rice to the incarcerated volunteers that were packing meals Thursday at Minnesota Correctional Facility-Faribault. (Colton Kemp/southernminn.com) Incarcerated people gave up their paid workdays to volunteer to pack meals with Meals From The Heart Thursday at the state prison. Packaging, at left, Bryan Arnesen and Jason Slattum, and, at top-right, Matthew Geist. (Colton Kemp/southernminn.com) Brandon Smith, an incarcerated person at the state prison in Faribault, tosses more meals into the box of finished ones for Meals From The Heart, which will bring them to Ruth’s House and Sarah’s House. (Colton Kemp/southernminn.com) From left, Aaron Lind-Pashina and Darius Woods package meals with Meals From The Heart Thursday morning in Minnesota Correctional Facility-Faribault. (Colton Kemp/southernminn.com) Pierce Heston seals one of the prepackaged meals alongside other incarcerated volunteers who gave up paid workdays at the Thursday at the Faribault state prison. (Colton Kemp/southernminn.com) Nutrient-rich ingredients, seen here, are combined into a single meal packet by volunteers organized by Meals From The Heart. (Colton Kemp/southernminn.com)",
